<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,734,1049]" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">
This species presents striking morphological similarities with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pic, 1912)" baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[907,1220,806,832]" class="Aves" family="Vireonidae" genus="Hylophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="167" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dentatifemur">
<emphasis box="[907,1082,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="167">Z. dentatifemur</emphasis>
(Pic, 1912)
</taxonomicName>
, including a longitudinal stripe of pubescence on the pronotum midline and the overall shape of the male genitalia. The shape of the tibiae, however, notably on the forelegs is unambiguously different.
</paragraph>
